comments.author: CJ Loveless

comments.text:
+Jamie Braly Agree big time. All else equal, *real* things look more real 
than fake things. 

I remember Star Trek II TWOK and how the ships *looked* real; as opposed to 
CGI renderings. Same thing with James Cameron's Titanic - they built half a 
real ship and only used CGI when necessary in the background.

Puppetry and models can be done badly, don't get me wrong, but I'd take 
skilled puppets & models over skilled CGI any day of the week.
